BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Accessibility Lunch & Learn: What do I do with all these PDFs? I
 nventorying and Assessing your PDF Backlog
LOCATION:Zoom (see registration link)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260407T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260407T130000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://washington.zoom.us/meeting/register/-_odhzhmTcut7-z-L0R9VQ
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:ats-events@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Worksh
 ops
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:Acces
 sible Technology Services: \nhttps://www.washington.edu/accesstech/
DTSTAMP:20260213T144709Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nAccessibility Contact: ats
 -events@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Workshops\nEvent sponsors: <a href="https:/
 /www.washington.edu/accesstech/" target="_blank">Accessible Technology S
 ervices</a>\nLink: https://washington.zoom.us/meeting/register/-_odhzhmT
 cut7-z-L0R9VQ\n\nIn this guided workshop\, you will receive tips and a s
 hared\, guided document to help you and your team take the first crucial
  steps toward creating strategy for dealing with your PDF backlog: inven
 tory and assessment. It's much easier to create a long-term plan for han
 dling the challenges posed by PDFs if you build a deeper awareness of ho
 w many you have\, how they were created\, and the purpose they serve. In
 ventorying and assessing your existing PDF backlog can also help you mak
 e informed choices about appropriate alternatives to PDFs in future work
 flow decisions. Please note: This is a strategy workshop\, so we won't b
 e covering how to remediate PDFs or demonstrating tools.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
