DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: Room 120 Lect
 ure Hall\nAccessibility Contact: ticket@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Screenings
 \nEvent sponsors: Presented in partnership with Meany Center\, the UW Sim
 pson Center for the Humanities\, and the UW Department of Dance.\nLink: 
 https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1a6I7UgpVOBwqqbWf-fIzDQ2ohcQNsr5GuqyOClV
 bV9c/viewform?edit_requested=true\n\nThe Grammy-nominated documentary Th
 e Music of Strangers\, follows members of the Ensemble as they gather in
  locations across the world\, exploring the ways art can both preserve t
 raditions and shape cultural evolution. Blending performance footage\, p
 ersonal interviews\, and archival film\, Oscar-winning director Morgan N
 eville and producer Caitrin Rogers focus on the personal journeys of a s
 mall group of Silkroad Ensemble mainstays — Kinan Azmeh (Syria)\, Kayhan
  Kalhor (Iran)\, Yo-Yo Ma (France/United States)\, Wu Man (China)\, and 
 Cristina Pato (Spain) — to chronicle passion\, talent\, and sacrifice. T
 hrough these moving individual stories\, the filmmakers paint a vivid po
 rtrait of a bold musical experiment and a global search for the ties tha
 t bind. Curriculum Guide: \nhttps://static1.squarespace.com/static/5b851
 632c258b41bb6cf9edc/t/5dadbbbe64fbcd1ae7cd8591/1571666888480/TMoS_Curric
 ulum_FINAL.pdf\n\nRegistration Link: \nhttps://docs.google.com/forms/d/1
 a6I7UgpVOBwqqbWf-fIzDQ2ohcQNsr5GuqyOClVbV9c/viewform?edit_requested=true
 
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
