X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgA%2A91ZxeA%2ATJYvJOOmcR1w4.jpg
DTSTAMP:20260305T170245Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Allen Lib
 rary (ALB)\nCampus room: Allen Auditorium\nAccessibility Contact: gwss@u
 w.edu\nEvent Types: Screenings\n\nGrrrilda Beausoleil is turning 50.\nAl
 l she wants is a reunion with her 1990s riot grrrl band—the one she aban
 doned just as they were about to make it big.\n\nWith a scrappy film cre
 w documenting the journey\, she navigates old wounds\, new-age platitude
 s\, and a San Francisco transformed by tech and displacement.\n\nThe ban
 d must decide whether they can trust Grrrilda again—and whether their DI
 Y roots of wheat paste\, stickers\, and zines can still build community 
 in a digital age.\n\nDubbed “SPINAL TAP with BIPOC and queers” by the Ch
 icago Reader\, the film is a hilarious improvised mockumentary that trea
 ts comedy as activism.\n\nAt its heart\, the production centers LGBTQ co
 mmunity building across generations—reconciling past and present\, passi
 ng the mic\, and finding solidarity through creativity.\n\nRead Maria Br
 eaux’s Femme Fatales profile.: \nhttps://www.filmfatales.org/directors/m
 ariabreaux/
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
