DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Douglas R
 esearch Conservatory (DRC)\nAccessibility Contact: urbhort@uw.edu\nPrese
 nter: Adelaide Nitroy\, Founder & Owner of Fancy Plants Seattle\nTicket 
 Link: https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_75c379f
 57711\nLink: https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_
 75c379f57711\n\nClass Cost: $40\nFinancial aid slots available on a firs
 t-come\, first-served basis\nREGISTER ONLINE: \nhttps://apps.ideal-logic
 .com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_75c379f57711\n\nHave you ever been te
 mpted by a good deal at a big box store\, only for your clearance rack p
 lant to die as soon as you bring it home? In this class\, we’ll learn ab
 out which plants are worth rehabbing\, and how to bring a struggling pla
 nt back to life. No experience necessary. All ages. Class fee covers all
  necessary supplies. \n\nAdelaide Nitroy\, founder and owner of Fancy Pl
 ants\, opened her business in 2022 with the hope of creating a safe and 
 inclusive environment for people to learn plants and begin their plant j
 ourney. Her background in biology and plant science gives a unique persp
 ective to provide scientific understanding of how plants have evolved\, 
 how plants work at a biological level\, and how plants can be grown succ
 essfully.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
