BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Liberation Book Club: Community\, Collaboration\, and Conflict
LOCATION:Art Building (ART)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T193000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus location";ID=30032;TYPE=CustomAsset:Ar
 t Building (ART)
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:Jacob L
 awrence Gallery
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:jacoblawrencegallery@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Specia
 l Events
DTSTAMP:20250916T122932Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Art Build
 ing (ART)\nCampus room: Jacob Lawrence Gallery\nAccessibility Contact: j
 acoblawrencegallery@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Special Events\n\nOur question 
 to consider: We are all in this together\, so\, how do we actually do th
 is work together?\n\n\n\nThis program is part of the Liberation Book Clu
 b at the Jacob Lawrence Gallery. This year-long program series hopes to 
 honor our commitment to social justice and to gather our community to th
 ink about the work of liberation through shared texts\, art\, film\, mus
 ic\, conversation\, and workshops. Unlike your traditional book club all
  the reading and study happens together\, so no need to prepare. Join us
  monthly as we approach the topic of liberation from a number of perspec
 tives. We look forward to being in community with you.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
