BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spring Colloquium: "Fronteras Embrujades: Tracing Tejana Feminis
 t Tensions and Speculative Statelessness on the Texas-Mexico Border\," p
 resented by Yasmine Gomez
LOCATION:Padelford Hall (PDL)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T170000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus location";ID=30032;TYPE=CustomAsset:Pa
 delford Hall (PDL)
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:PDL B11
 0 G
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:gwss@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Lectur
 es/Seminars
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgBUz-QmprWhEu7aZ1NBAim2.jpg
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Target Audience";ID=42285;TYPE=SingleLine:Fre
 e and open to the public
DTSTAMP:20260325T142401Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Padelford
  Hall (PDL)\nCampus room: PDL B110 G\nAccessibility Contact: gwss@uw.edu
 \nEvent Types: Lectures/Seminars\nTarget Audience: Free and open to the 
 public\n\nPresenter: Yasmine Gomez\, GWSS PhD Student\nModerator: Royalt
 i Richardson\, GWSS PhD Student\n\nFramed by her upcoming candidacy exam
 s\, this presentation introduces Yasmine’s doctoral research on borderla
 nd feminisms. Fronteras Embrujadas interrogates the contested boundaries
  of Tejana activism\, cultural production\, and collective memory to exa
 mine the current political moment in the Rio Grande Valley of Texas.\n\n
 This research examines how borderland identities are negotiated through 
 ongoing methods of state-sanctioned violence/surveillance through techno
 colonialism and spaces of detainment\, while looking to Tejana Speculati
 ve archives to reconceptualize the radical position of place in activism
 .\n\nFurther\, this work considers the role of global borderlands in dev
 eloping contemporary transnational feminist archives of solidarity that 
 center anti-extractivism as core principles of feminist activism movemen
 t.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
