DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Smith Hal
 l (SMI)\nAccessibility Contact: hbcls@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Special Event
 s\,Student Activities\,Workshops\nLink: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/
 e/1FAIpQLSezo8cR21X4JuAWREmanvk77Mgw7VLS3hwaz8iSO9VgU_kr0g/viewform\n\nT
 he Harry Bridges Center for Labor Studies is hosting a zine-making party
  on Thursday\, April 16th\, 5pm-7pm at Smith Hall\, Room 320 (History Lo
 unge)! RSVP here: \nhttps://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSezo8cR21X4
 JuAWREmanvk77Mgw7VLS3hwaz8iSO9VgU_kr0g/viewform\n\nThis quarter is the f
 irst quarter we will be constructing a community-built labor zine! This 
 zine is intended to be a visionary collection that\, through its creatio
 n\, allows individuals to explore their relation to labor\, labor moveme
 nts\, and people’s struggles. The collective outcome will showcase the d
 istinctiveness of our struggles while unifying us around a vision of lib
 eration.\n\nThe Bridges Center recognizes that labor occurs everywhere u
 nder many conditions - at home\, in the workplace\, waged and unwaged\, 
 organized and unorganized. What you choose to create is entirely up to y
 ou\; it could be poetry\, prose\, a drawing\, collage\, painting\, or an
 y combination.\n\nWe welcome all participants\, including UW staff\, stu
 dents\, faculty\, and community members!
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
