BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fundamentals For Startups: Cofounder Relationships- Building the
  Partnership That Builds Your Company
LOCATION:Startup Hall - 1100 NE Campus Parkway\, 2nd floor (take elevato
 r\, opens at 11:30 AM)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260417T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260417T130000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://luma.com/cmevents
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Ong
 oing event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:Condon 
 Hall\, 2nd floor (take elevator\, opens at 11:30 AM)
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:dso@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Lectur
 es/Seminars
DTSTAMP:20260318T090306Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Ongoing event\nCampus room: Condon Hall\, 2n
 d floor (take elevator\, opens at 11:30 AM)\nAccessibility Contact: dso@
 uw.edu\nEvent Types: Lectures/Seminars\nLink: https://luma.com/cmevents
 \n\nPlease register for this event on our Luma calendar: https://luma.com
 /cmevents. ​Elevators and doors open at 11:30 AM and will close promptly
  at 12:15 PM.\n\nLecture:\n\nOne of the biggest factors that can make or
  break a startup’s success is the cofounder relationship. Yet many found
 ers focus on operations while overlooking the psychological and interper
 sonal dynamics that quietly shape everything from decision‑making to cul
 ture.\n\n​This one‑hour lecture breaks down the hidden work of building 
 and sustaining a healthy\, resilient cofounder partnership\, including:
 \n	 - ​Why your partnership matters more than your product: How founder d
 ynamics influence execution\, trust\, and long‑term viability.	\n - ​Fin
 ding the right cofounder: How to look beyond technical skills to build a
  partnership that will last	\n - ​Creating explicit agreements: Roles\, 
 expectations\, decision rights\, and the conversations founders avoid un
 til they become problems.	\n - ​Using your relationship as cultural blue
 print: The way you communicate\, disagree\, and repair becomes the templ
 ate your entire team follows.	\n - ​Addressing emotional debt: How unspo
 ken frustrations accumulate—and how to clear them before they become str
 uctural cracks.\n\n-----------------------------------------------------
 ---------------------------\nSpeaker:\n\nT.A. McCann is the CEO of Lev. 
 He is a serial entrepreneur and Managing Director at Pioneer Square Labs
 \, a leading venture studio in Seattle\, WA. He was the founder and CEO 
 of Senosis (acquired by Google)\, Gist (acquired by Blackberry)\, and Ri
 val IQ (acquired by Netbase)\, in addition to a few other companies that
  were not so lucky. Previously\, he was an EIR at Polaris Venture Partne
 rs and Vulcan Capital\, where he built Vulcan Labs and Providence Health
  Services\, focusing on quantified health ideas and investments. He also
  held senior roles at Microsoft\, leading Exchange and the Mobile Servic
 es divisions.\n\n​In addition to his own startup experience\, he is an a
 ctive angel investor in companies including SkillJar\, CreativeLive\, As
 sist\, XMPT\, and Vendor Hawk\, and on the board of Guidant Financial\, 
 Volt Athletics\, and Zero Health.  He is also an adjunct professor at th
 e University of Washington Foster School of Business and an active TechS
 tars mentor. \n\nPrior to his startup career\, he was a professional sai
 lor\, having competed in 2 America's Cups (one won\, one lost) and the W
 hitbread Round the World Race. He holds a degree in mechanical engineeri
 ng from Purdue University\, where he attended on a full swimming scholar
 ship.\n-----------------------------------------------------------------
 ---------------\nAbout Fundamentals for Startups:\n\nFundamentals for St
 artups is a weekly one-hour lecture series featuring notable experts who
  share startup-related information\, experience\, and insights with our 
 entrepreneurial community. From raising capital to scaling to exit strat
 egies\, these seasoned guest speakers deliver valuable content designed 
 to help startups and entrepreneurs thrive.\n\nThese lectures are open to
  the public and you do not have to be currently affiliated with the UW o
 r a startup to join. Lunch is provided while supplies last. Advanced reg
 istration required. Please note\, we are no longer livestreaming these s
 essions.\n\n​Elevators and doors open at 11:30 AM and will close promptl
 y at 12:15 PM. Don't be late!\n\nWe hope you can join us!
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/198936630
X-TRUMBA-LINK:https://www.washington.edu/calendar/?trumbaEmbed=view%3dev
 ent%26eventid%3d198936630
END:VEVENT
