 Melinda Gates Center For Computer Science & Engineering Room 371\; Unive
 rsity of Washington\, 3800 E Stevens Way NE\, Seattle\, WA 98195
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:finchkn@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Inform
 ation Sessions\,Student Activities\,Workshops
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgBhKskS4KQY7Gnhr-1QElgn.jpg
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:NVIDI
 A: https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/\nUWIT Research Computing: \nhttps://it.
 uw.edu/guides/research/\neScience Institute: \nhttps://escience.washingt
 on.edu/\nOffice of Research: \nhttps://www.washington.edu/research/
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Target Audience";ID=42285;TYPE=SingleLine:fac
 ulty\, staff\, students\, postdocs\, researchers
DTSTAMP:20260313T201927Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Bill & Me
 linda Gates Center for Computer Science & Engineering (CSE2)\nCampus roo
 m: Bill & Melinda Gates Center For Computer Science & Engineering Room 3
 71\; University of Washington\, 3800 E Stevens Way NE\, Seattle\, WA 981
 95\nAccessibility Contact: finchkn@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Information Sess
 ions\,Student Activities\,Workshops\nEvent sponsors: <a href="https://ww
 w.nvidia.com/en-us/" target="_blank">NVIDIA</a><br /><a href="https://it
 .uw.edu/guides/research/" target="_blank">UWIT Research Computing</a><br
  /><a href="https://escience.washington.edu/" target="_blank">eScience I
 nstitute</a><br /><a href="https://www.washington.edu/research/" target=
 "_blank">Office of Research</a>\nTarget Audience: faculty\, staff\, stud
 ents\, postdocs\, researchers\nLink: https://forms.office.com/r/VQiyYeBP
 WQ\n\n&#x1F449\; Register now — limited spots!: \nhttps://forms.office.c
 om/r/VQiyYeBPWQ\nregistration QR code\n\nDate: Tuesday April 21\, 2026\n
 Time: 10am-12pm \nLocation: Room 371 CSE2/Gate Hall (Bill & Melinda Gate
 s Center For Computer Science & Engineering\; University of Washington\,
  3800 E Stevens Way NE\, Seattle\, WA 98195) or virtual.\nHybrid: YES! J
 oin us in person or on Zoom (authentication required\; only official dom
 ains permitted). \n\nThis NVIDIA-led training focuses on scaling GPU wor
 kloads with PyTorch Distributed Data Parallel (DDP) : \nhttps://docs.pyt
 orch.org/tutorials/beginner/dist_overview.html#applying-parallelism-to-s
 cale-your-modeland using NVIDIA Nsight tools to understand and improve p
 erformance. The session is designed for practitioners who already have a
  working PyTorch training script and want to move toward efficient multi
 -GPU execution while learning how to profile\, diagnose bottlenecks\, an
 d interpret performance signals in a principled way.\n\nWe’ll cover reco
 mmended DDP patterns for scaling training\, common pitfalls that limit t
 hroughput\, and how to integrate Nsight profiling into your workflow. Th
 rough guided exercises\, participants will practice launching and scalin
 g jobs\, collecting profiling traces\, and using insights from Nsight to
  reason about GPU utilization\, CPU/GPU interaction\, and performance co
 nstraints.\n\nThe hands-on portion of this workshop will be applied to T
 illicum\, UW's GPU Cluster: \nhttps://uwconnect.uw.edu/it?id=kb_article_
 view&sysparm_article=KB0036077. \n\nPrerequisites: \n	 - Working knowled
 ge of PyTorch training basics: \nhttps://docs.pytorch.org/tutorials/begi
 nner/basics/intro.html: tensors\, model/optimizer/loss\, dataloaders\, t
 raining loop\, saving/loading checkpoints.	\n - Comfort running code fro
 m the command line: \nhttps://github.com/UWrc/linux-fundamentals (or in 
 a Jupyter environment) and editing scripts.	\n - Basic GPU familiarity: 
 what a GPU is used for\, moving tensors/models to CUDA\, reading basic C
 UDA OOM / device errors.\nTillicum prerequisites: \n	 - Tillicum Onboard
 ing Tutorial: \nhttps://github.com/UWrc/tillicum-onboarding	\n - Tillicu
 m Slurm Tutorial: \nhttps://github.com/UWrc/tillicum-slurm	\n - Managing
  Python Environments with Conda in Jupyter Tutorial: \nhttps://github.co
 m/UWrc/jupyter-tutorial
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
