BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FOOD SYSTEMS SEMINAR:  From Food Stamps to SNAP: A Political and
  Social History
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T142000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://foodsystems.uw.edu/seminar/
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:Check M
 y Plan for location
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:nutr@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Lectur
 es/Seminars
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:Schoo
 l of Public Health Food Systems\, Nutrition\, and Health program
DTSTAMP:20260320T104003Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: Check My Plan
  for location\nAccessibility Contact: nutr@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Lectures
 /Seminars\nEvent sponsors: School of Public Health Food Systems\, Nutrit
 ion\, and Health program\nLink: https://foodsystems.uw.edu/seminar/\n\nF
 rom Food Stamps to SNAP: A Political and Social History\n\nSpeaker:\nTra
 cy Roof\, associate professor\, political science\, University of Richmo
 nd\n\nThis session is offered as part of the weekly series on: "Food and
  Nutrition Security: Understanding\, Measuring and Reimagining Nutrition
  Assistance in the U.S."\n\nIf you care about how food-related safety ne
 ts succeed—or fail—this seminar offers tools to understand today’s lands
 cape and imagine a better one.\n\nHow is food and nutrition security def
 ined\, measured\, and funded in the United States—and how do those choic
 es shape real‑world hunger and health?\n\nThis seminar explores the nati
 on’s major nutrition assistance programs—SNAP\, WIC\, school meals\, and
  the charitable food system. Learn how these programs work\, who they re
 ach\, and why their impacts vary across states and communities.\n\nAll U
 W students\, faculty\, and staff are welcome to attend the seminar. Chec
 k MyPlan for location information.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
