DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: Zoom Webinar
 \nAccessibility Contact: UW Interprofessional Continuing Education  ipce@
 uw.edu\nEvent Types: Conferences\,Lectures/Seminars\,Meetings\nEvent spo
 nsors: Department of Cardiology\nOffice of Continuing Medical Education
 \nOffice of Faculty Affairs\nUW School of Medicine\nTarget Audience: Prim
 ary care physicians and providers\, nurses\, and allied health professio
 nals that work in primary\nLink: https://uw.cloud-cme.com/MJ2611\n\nThis
  course is tailored for a primary care audience and is intended to provi
 de practical\, up-to-date information on commonly encountered cardiovasc
 ular diseases. World-class faculty from the University of Washington Sch
 ool of Medicine will teach participants using case-based lectures and an
  audience response system to encourage interactive dialogue. Recent guid
 elines for hypertension\, cholesterol management\, primary prevention of
  heart disease\, and heart failure will be reviewed. Everyday primary ca
 re topics including diagnosis and treatment of coronary artery disease\,
  congestive heart failure\, valvular heart disease and supraventricular 
 arrhythmias\, including atrial fibrillation\, will be covered. Practical
  issues regarding use of new anticoagulants will be discussed. Appropria
 teness of cardiac testing will be discussed during lectures on the cardi
 ovascular physical exam and the evaluation of chest pain with stress tes
 ting and coronary CT imaging. The day will conclude with a comprehensive
  Q&A session lead by the course chairs.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
