BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fundamentals For Startups: Building & Hiring Globally- Navigatin
 g Startups & Talent on U.S. Visas
LOCATION:Startup Hall - 1100 NE Campus Parkway\, 2nd floor (take elevato
 r\, opens at 11:30 AM)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T130000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://luma.com/cmevents
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Ong
 oing event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:Condon 
 Hall\, 2nd floor (take elevator\, opens at 11:30 AM)
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:dso@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Lectur
 es/Seminars
DTSTAMP:20260318T090357Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Ongoing event\nCampus room: Condon Hall\, 2n
 d floor (take elevator\, opens at 11:30 AM)\nAccessibility Contact: dso@
 uw.edu\nEvent Types: Lectures/Seminars\nLink: https://luma.com/cmevents
 \n\nPlease register for this event on our Luma calendar: https://luma.com
 /cmevents. ​Elevators and doors open at 11:30 AM and will close promptly
  at 12:15 PM.\n\nLecture:\n\nMany founders and early teams in the U.S. s
 tartup ecosystem are navigating immigration questions alongside building
  their companies. This session explores how founders can build and opera
 te a startup while maintaining visa status\, and how companies can hire 
 international talent responsibly.\n\n​We will walk through common visa p
 athways such as O-1\, H-1B\, EB-1A\, and EB-2 NIW\, explain what founder
 s and operators can and cannot do under different statuses\, and discuss
  practical strategies for hiring global talent. The goal is to help earl
 y-stage founders understand the immigration mechanics that shape hiring 
 decisions\, company formation\, and long-term planning.\n---------------
 -----------------------------------------------------------------\nSpeak
 er:\n\nPriyanka Kulkarni is the Founder and CEO of Casium\, a company fo
 cused on helping global talent and innovative companies navigate the U.S
 . immigration system with greater clarity and transparency.\n\n​As an im
 migrant founder herself\, Priyanka built Casium to simplify how high-ski
 lled professionals and startups approach complex visa pathways. Through 
 Casium’s platform and legal team\, the company helps individuals and org
 anizations prepare well-documented visa petitions that clearly present t
 heir achievements and qualifications to USCIS.\n------------------------
 --------------------------------------------------------\nAbout Fundamen
 tals for Startups:\n\nFundamentals for Startups is a weekly one-hour lec
 ture series featuring notable experts who share startup-related informat
 ion\, experience\, and insights with our entrepreneurial community. From
  raising capital to scaling to exit strategies\, these seasoned guest sp
 eakers deliver valuable content designed to help startups and entreprene
 urs thrive.\n\nThese lectures are open to the public and you do not have
  to be currently affiliated with the UW or a startup to join. Lunch is p
 rovided while supplies last. Advanced registration required. Please note
 \, we are no longer livestreaming these sessions.\n\n​Elevators and door
 s open at 11:30 AM and will close promptly at 12:15 PM. Don't be late!\n
 \nWe hope you can join us!
