BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:UWCFD Lunch & Learn: From Birds to Bees to Wild Lands: Caring fo
 r Our Planet\, Close to Home
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260428T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260428T130000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Online Meeting Link";ID=54756;TYPE=Url:https:
 //wholeu.admin.washington.edu/uwnetid/twuext/EventDetail.aspx?regid=&eve
 ntid=1925&eventsessionid=1862
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:sky0428@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Inform
 ation Sessions
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgBroOb3i45UCw9Oo5qy23ti.jpg
DTSTAMP:20260327T140317Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nOnline Meeting Link: https
 ://wholeu.admin.washington.edu/uwnetid/twuext/EventDetail.aspx?regid=&ev
 entid=1925&eventsessionid=1862\nAccessibility Contact: sky0428@uw.edu\nE
 vent Types: Information Sessions\n\nIn celebration of Earth Day\, we inv
 ite you to a special Lunch & Learn highlighting local nonprofits dedicat
 ed to protecting and preserving our environment. In the spirit of this y
 ear’s theme\, Our Power\, Our Planet\, we’re excited to welcome three in
 spiring organizations making a meaningful impact close to home:\n\nBirds
  Connect Seattle: https://birdsconnectsea.org/ brings its mission to lif
 e through urban and regional initiatives that spark curiosity\, deepen u
 nderstanding\, and inspire protection of birds—both within our local com
 munity and beyond.\n\nBackyard Beekeepers Association: \nhttps://www.bac
 kyard-beekeepers.org/ educates the public about the many benefits of bee
 keeping while promoting the health of honey bees and native pollinators.
  Through classes\, presentations\, and conferences\, they offer learning
  opportunities for everyone—from curious beginners to experienced beekee
 pers.\n\nWashington Wild : https://wawild.org/works to protect and resto
 re Washington’s wild lands and waters through advocacy\, education\, and
  civic engagement. Founded in 1979 as the Washington Wilderness Coalitio
 n\, the organization has helped safeguard nearly 3 million acres of wild
 erness across the state.\n\nWe hope you’ll join us to learn more about c
 aring for this beautiful place we call home - and how\, together\, we ca
 n keep it healthy and green. Register here: \nhttps://wholeu.admin.washi
 ngton.edu/uwnetid/twuext/EventDetail.aspx?regid=&eventid=1925&eventsessi
 onid=1862.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
