BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FOOD SYSTEMS SEMINAR:  SNAP Food Restrictions: Rationale and Sta
 te Rollout
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260506T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260506T142000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://foodsystems.uw.edu/seminar/
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:Check M
 y Plan for location
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:nutr@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Lectur
 es/Seminars
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:Schoo
 l of Public Health Food Systems\, Nutrition\, and Health program
DTSTAMP:20260327T082705Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: Check My Plan
  for location\nAccessibility Contact: nutr@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Lectures
 /Seminars\nEvent sponsors: School of Public Health Food Systems\, Nutrit
 ion\, and Health program\nLink: https://foodsystems.uw.edu/seminar/\n\nS
 NAP Food Restrictions: Rationale and State Rollout\n\nSpeaker:\nAlyssa M
 oran\, deputy director\, Center for Food and Nutrition Policy\, Universi
 ty of Pennsylvania\n\nThis session is offered as part of the weekly seri
 es on: "Food and Nutrition Security: Understanding\, Measuring and Reima
 gining Nutrition Assistance in the U.S."\n\nIf you care about how food-r
 elated safety nets succeed—or fail—this seminar offers tools to understa
 nd today’s landscape and imagine a better one.\n\nHow is food and nutrit
 ion security defined\, measured\, and funded in the United States—and ho
 w do those choices shape real‑world hunger and health?\n\nThis seminar e
 xplores the nation’s major nutrition assistance programs—SNAP\, WIC\, sc
 hool meals\, and the charitable food system. Learn how these programs wo
 rk\, who they reach\, and why their impacts vary across states and commu
 nities.\n\nAll UW students\, faculty\, and staff are welcome to attend t
 he seminar. Check MyPlan for location information.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/199097599
