SUMMARY:Distinguished Lecture Series: Kevin Weil - Accelerating Science 
 with AI
LOCATION:Gates Center (CSE2)\, G20 | Amazon Auditorium
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260507T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260507T163000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://www.cs.washington.edu/events/colloquia/details?id=3382
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:Gates C
 enter (CSE2)\, G20 | Amazon Auditorium
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:dso@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Lectur
 es/Seminars
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgDIe9S8vzqHGCfpQevTbPCY.jpg
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:Paul 
 G. Allen School of Computer Science & Engineering\nwww.cs.washington.edu
 \n206-543-0998
DTSTAMP:20260106T111625Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: Gates Center 
 (CSE2)\, G20 | Amazon Auditorium\nAccessibility Contact: dso@uw.edu\nEve
 nt Types: Lectures/Seminars\nEvent sponsors: Paul G. Allen School of Com
 puter Science &amp\; Engineering\nwww.cs.washington.edu\n206-543-0998\nL
 ink: https://www.cs.washington.edu/events/colloquia/details?id=3382\n\nA
 bstract is forthcoming.\n\nBIO:\nKevin Weil is VP of OpenAI for Science
 \, focused on building the next great scientific instrument: an AI-powere
 d platform that accelerates scientific discovery. Previously\, Kevin ser
 ved as the Chief Product Officer at OpenAI\, where he led the teams turn
 ing frontier models into products like ChatGPT\, Codex\, and the OpenAI 
 API.\n\nBefore joining OpenAI\, Kevin was the President\, Product and Bu
 siness at Planet Labs. He was previously the co-founder of the Libra cry
 ptocurrency and VP of Product for Novi at Facebook\, VP of Product at In
 stagram and SVP of Product at Twitter. Earlier in his career\, Kevin hel
 d software engineering and data science roles at Cooliris\, Tropos Netwo
 rks\, Microsoft Research and the Stanford Linear Accelerator Center.\n\n
 Kevin graduated summa cum laude in physics and mathematics from Harvard 
 University and has an M.S. in physics from Stanford University. He is a 
 term member of the Council on Foreign Relations (CFR) and serves on the 
 boards of Cisco and The Nature Conservancy. In his spare time\, he is an
  avid ultramarathon runner\, racing distances up to 100 miles.\n \nThis 
 lecture will be recorded and streamed live on the Allen School's YouTube
  channel: \nhttps://www.youtube.com/@uwcse (https://www.youtube.com/@uwc
 se)\, unless otherwise noted. The link will be available on that page on
 e hour prior to the event.\n\n\nThe University of Washington is committe
 d to providing access\, equal opportunity and reasonable accommodation i
 n its services\, programs\, activities\, education and employment for in
 dividuals with disabilities. Live captioning will be provided for this e
 vent. To request disability accommodation such as ASL interpretation\, c
 ontact the Disability Services Office at least ten days in advance of th
 e event at: (206) 543-6450/V\, (206) 543-6452/TTY\, (206) 685-7264 (FAX)
 \, or email at dso@u.washington.edu.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
