 ook.com/share/19QV8cxcbm/
DTSTAMP:20250922T150639Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Meany Hal
 l (MNY)\nAccessibility Contact: ticket@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Performances
 \,Student Activities\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/share/19QV8cxcb
 m/\nLink: https://meanycenter.org/tickets/2026-05/production/min-kwon\n
 \nPianist Min Kwon presents a selection of pieces from her America/Beauti
 ful project that commissioned 70 American composers to create a variatio
 n on the patriotic hymn\, “America the Beautiful.” Out of this\, Kwon pa
 ints a sonic and visual picture of her adopted country in all of its spr
 awling complexity\, and ultimately looks for the beauty at the core of t
 he American experiment and its credo of e pluribus unum (out of many\, o
 ne).
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
