BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FOOD SYSTEMS SEMINAR:  Food Banks in the U.S.: Roles\, Limits\, 
 and Realities
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260513T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260513T142000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://foodsystems.uw.edu/seminar/
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:Check M
 y Plan for location
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:nutr@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Lectur
 es/Seminars
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:Schoo
 l of Public Health Food Systems\, Nutrition\, and Health program
DTSTAMP:20260320T104222Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: Check My Plan
  for location\nAccessibility Contact: nutr@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Lectures
 /Seminars\nEvent sponsors: School of Public Health Food Systems\, Nutrit
 ion\, and Health program\nLink: https://foodsystems.uw.edu/seminar/\n\nF
 ood Banks in the U.S.: Roles\, Limits\, and Realities\n\nSpeaker:\nJen M
 uzia\, executive director\, Ballard Food Bank\n\nThis session is offered
  as part of the weekly series on: "Food and Nutrition Security: Understa
 nding\, Measuring and Reimagining Nutrition Assistance in the U.S."\n\nI
 f you care about how food-related safety nets succeed—or fail—this semin
 ar offers tools to understand today’s landscape and imagine a better one
 .\n\nHow is food and nutrition security defined\, measured\, and funded 
 in the United States—and how do those choices shape real‑world hunger an
 d health?\n\nThis seminar explores the nation’s major nutrition assistan
 ce programs—SNAP\, WIC\, school meals\, and the charitable food system. 
 Learn how these programs work\, who they reach\, and why their impacts v
 ary across states and communities.\n\nAll UW students\, faculty\, and st
 aff are welcome to attend the seminar. Check MyPlan for location informa
 tion.
