DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: UW Tower 
 Complex (SFCO)\nCampus room: UW Tower South Cafeteria Mezzanine Level 43
 33 Brooklyn Ave NE Seattle\, WA 98105\nAccessibility Contact: finchkn@uw
 .edu\nEvent Types: Academics\,Special Events\,Student Activities\,Worksh
 ops\nEvent sponsors: <a href="https://research.ibm.com/quantum-computing
 " target="_blank">IBM Quantum</a><br /><a href="https://it.uw.edu/guides
 /research/" target="_blank">UWIT Research Computing</a><br /><a href="ht
 tps://www.washington.edu/research/" target="_blank">Office of Research</
 a><br /><a href="https://depts.washington.edu/uwrcc/" target="_blank">Re
 search Computing Club</a>\nTarget Audience: faculty\, staff\, students\,
  postdocs\, researchers\nLink: https://forms.office.com/r/RMB5RY15BK\n\n
 &#x1F449\; Register now — limited spots!: \nhttps://forms.office.com/r/R
 MB5RY15BK\n\nregistration QR code\n\nQuantum Hackathon with IBM Quantum
 \n\nJoin us on Thursday\, May 14\, from 10:00 AM-5 PM for a quantum compu
 ting hackathon on Quantum Machine Learning co-organized with IBM Quantum
 . This hands-on coding event will explore quantum computing through guid
 ed challenges and collaborative problem-solving. Participants will work 
 with IBM Quantum tools to experiment with quantum algorithms on real har
 dware and simulators. This event is open to anyone interested in learnin
 g by doing—no previous quantum experience required. Lunch will be provid
 ed for participants. \n\nTo make the day more productive\, please ensure
  you bring a working laptop and follow these steps:\n	 - Create an IBM Q
 uantum Cloud account &#x1F449\; Set up guide: \nhttps://quantum.cloud.ib
 m.com/docs/en/guides/cloud-setup	\n - Install a working Python environme
 nt where you can use Qiskit 	\n		 - &#x1F449\; Online Lab Environments G
 uides: \nhttps://quantum.cloud.ibm.com/docs/en/guides/online-lab-environ
 ments		\n - &#x1F449\; Qiskit Guide: \nhttps://quantum.cloud.ibm.com/doc
 s/en/guides/install-qiskit	\n	\nJoin UWIT Research Computing Office Hour
 s if you require assistance:\n	 - Cloud Computing Office Hours - Every o
 ther Tuesday at 10am on Zoom. Find the time that works for you.: \nhttps
 ://calendar.washington.edu/sea_uwit-rc	\n - HPC Office Hours - Every Wed
 nesday at 2pm on Zoom.: \nhttps://washington.zoom.us/meeting/register/tJ
 Mpce6vrz8sEtR5miKvhsQiXANt6lBORFTu	\n - HPC Office Hours - Every Thursda
 y at 2pm in eScience (address: WRF Data Science Studio\, UW Physics/Astr
 onomy Tower\, 6th Floor\, 3910 15th Ave NE\, Seattle\, WA 98195)\n\nIf y
 ou’d like to get familiar with quantum machine learning ahead of time\, 
 you’re welcome to explore this IBM Quantum Learning course: \nhttps://qu
 antum.cloud.ibm.com/learning/en/courses/quantum-machine-learning.\n\nDue
  to the interactive natural of this event\, remote attendance is not sup
 ported. \n\nVenue Notes: \n	 - Bring your Husky card to pass through the
  gate in the foyer of the UW Tower. External guests should contact the e
 vent accessibility contact at least 24 hours before the event--UW Tower 
 security will check you in. 	\n - Take the Elevator to Level M for "Mezz
 anine"	\n - Follow signs pointing the way! Or use the map below\nvenue m
 ap showing the path to follow on the mezzanine level
