DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Bill & Me
 linda Gates Center for Computer Science & Engineering (CSE2)\nCampus roo
 m: Bill & Melinda Gates Center For Computer Science & Engineering Room 3
 71\; University of Washington\, 3800 E Stevens Way NE\, Seattle\, WA 981
 95\nAccessibility Contact: finchkn@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Information Sess
 ions\,Student Activities\,Workshops\nEvent sponsors: <a href="https://aw
 s.amazon.com/legal/marketingentities/" target="_blank">Amazon Web Servic
 es</a><br /><a href="https://it.uw.edu/guides/research/" target="_blank"
 >UWIT Research Computing</a><br /><a href="https://escience.washington.e
 du/" target="_blank">eScience Institute</a><br /><a href="https://www.wa
 shington.edu/research/" target="_blank">Office of Research</a>\nTarget A
 udience: faculty\, staff\, students\, postdocs\, researchers\nLink: http
 s://forms.office.com/r/xRpzpLZ6My\n\n&#x1F449\; Register now — limited s
 pots! : \nhttps://forms.office.com/r/xRpzpLZ6My\nregistration QR code\n
 \nDate: Tuesday May 19\, 2026\nTime: 10am-4pm \nLunch &#x1F37D\;: Provide
 d (sponsored by AWS)\nLocation: Room 371 CSE2/Gate Hall (Bill & Melinda 
 Gates Center For Computer Science & Engineering\; University of Washingt
 on\, 3800 E Stevens Way NE\, Seattle\, WA 98195) or virtual.\nHybrid: YE
 S! Join us in person or on Zoom (authentication required\; only official
  domains permitted). \n\nWe’re excited to host a full-day\, hands-on wor
 kshop with AWS showcasing Kiro\, an AI-native coding assistant built to 
 accelerate software development without sacrificing code quality or arch
 itectural rigor.\n\nIn this hands-on session\, you'll explore the capabi
 lities of Kiro\, an AI-powered assistant designed to accelerate software
  development and cloud operations. You'll experience firsthand how AI as
 sistance can boost productivity and help you build\, deploy\, and operat
 e applications more efficiently. From setting up Kiro in your developmen
 t environment to completing a real-world coding challenge\, this worksho
 p provides a comprehensive journey through the development lifecycle wit
 h AI assistance.\n\nThis event is ideal for software developers\, engine
 ers\, and students who want practical experience using AI tools to deliv
 er production-quality software. No prior experience with Kiro is require
 d.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
