BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Public Lecture | Jacob Daniels | The Jews of Edirne: The End of 
 Ottoman Europe and the Arrival of Borders
LOCATION:Student Union Building (HUB)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260519T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260519T180000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus location";ID=30032;TYPE=CustomAsset:St
 udent Union Building (HUB)
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:HUB 145
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:jewishst@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Academ
 ics
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgArCZo2qbivWgkSlUkKQbbV.jpg
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:UW Se
 phardic Studies Program\nUW Middle East Center\nUW Stroum Center for Jew
 ish Studies
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Target Audience";ID=42285;TYPE=SingleLine:Ope
 n to public. Registration required.
DTSTAMP:20260402T135622Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Student U
 nion Building (HUB)\nCampus room: HUB 145\nAccessibility Contact: jewish
 st@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Academics\nEvent sponsors: UW Sephardic Studies 
 Program\nUW Middle East Center\nUW Stroum Center for Jewish Studies\nTar
 get Audience: Open to public. Registration required.\n\nJoin us in welco
 ming visiting author and scholar Jacob Daniels\, discussing his new book
 \, The Jews of Edirne: The End of the Ottoman Europe and the Arrival of 
 Borders. \n\nAt the turn of the twentieth century\, the city of Edirne w
 as a bustling center linking Istanbul to Ottoman Europe. It was also the
  capital of Edirne Province—among the most religiously diverse regions o
 f the Ottoman Empire. But by 1923\, the city had become a Turkish border
  town\, and the province had lost much of its non-Muslim population. Wit
 h this book\, Jacob Daniels explores how one of the world's largest Seph
 ardi communities dealt with the encroachment of modern borders.\n\nJacob
  Daniels is Assistant Professor of Instruction and Assistant Director of
  the Schusterman Center for Jewish Studies at The University of Texas at
  Austin. He received his Ph.D. in History at Stanford University in 2022
 .
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
