DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Center fo
 r Urban Horticulture Complex (CUH)\nAccessibility Contact: urbhort@uw.ed
 u\nPresenter: Lea Dyga\, Oxbow Farm Native Plant Nursery Manager\nContac
 t Information: urbhort@uw.edu\nTicket Link: https://apps.ideal-logic.com
 /uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_5a8e4f17ceef\nLink: https://apps.ideal-lo
 gic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_5a8e4f17ceef\n\nCost: $30\, advanc
 ed registration required\nFinancial aid available on a first-come\, firs
 t-served basis\nREGISTER ONLINE: \nhttps://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key
 =2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_5a8e4f17ceef\nJoin us for an exploration of the ed
 ible and medicinal plants native to the PNW. In this interactive class\,
  you'll learn how to identify\, grow\, harvest\, and utilize 10+ local p
 lants with nourishing and healing properties. Throughout the session\, y
 ou'll gain practical knowledge on how to incorporate these plants into y
 our daily life and learn how to cultivate them in your own garden. Plus
 \, you'll have the chance to sample a variety of edible plants and create
  a custom tea blend to take home. \n\nThis class will be taught by Lea D
 yga\, Oxbow Farm’s Native Plant Nursery Manager\, formerly the SER-UW Na
 tive Plant Nursery Manager.
