DTSTAMP:20260313T105111Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nAccessibility Contact: lec
 tures@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Diversity Equity Inclusion\,Lectures/Seminars
 \nEvent sponsors: Paul Allen School of Computer Science and Engineering
 \, School of Law\, Disabilities\, Opportunities\, Internetworking\, and T
 echnology (DO-IT)\, School of Social Work\, Disability Studies Program\,
  Center for Research and Education on Accessible Technology and Experien
 ces (CREATE)\, The Graduate School\nLink: https://www.washington.edu/lec
 tures/events/what-does-law-mean-in-crisis-how-crip-feminist-technoscienc
 e-will-save-us-presented-by-the-office-of-public-lectures/\n\nIn a world
  ablaze with crisis\, this lecture explores crip feminist technoscience 
 as a tool for survival and resistance—offering disabled wisdom to reimag
 ine justice\, regulate AI\, and challenge empire\, white supremacy\, and
  late-stage capitalism through a disability justice lens.
