X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgASCK19RQoXiOVINtoxO-hh.jpg
DTSTAMP:20260128T100723Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Floyd and
  Delores Jones Playhouse (PHT)\nAccessibility Contact: ticket@uw.edu\nEv
 ent Types: Performances\nLink: https://drama.washington.edu/events/2026-
 05-21/everybody\n\nAt “God’s” command\, “Death” summons “Everybody” to g
 o on the long and difficult journey to give a presentation to “God” on E
 verybody’s life and why they have lived it the way that they have. Every
 body wants to bring along a friend\, and Death says it’s fine if Everybo
 dy can find someone to volunteer. Pulitzer Prize winning playwright Bran
 den Jacob Jenkins based the play on the 15th century morality play\, Eve
 ryman. Professor Chi-wang Yang directs this production in which each nig
 ht the performers’ roles will be determined by a lottery to determine wh
 ich role will be played by which performer.\, Everybody reveals to us th
 e value of our relationships and how to live with intention amid uncerta
 inty.\n\nFor tickets\, go to artsevents.washington.edu: \nhttp://artseve
 nts.washington.edu
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
