SUMMARY:3rd Annual Seattle Sudden Cardiac Death Symposium
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260530T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260530T180000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://uw.cloud-cme.com/MJ2609
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:South L
 ake Union Campus - Orin Smith Auditorium
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:UW Interprofessional Continuing Education  ipce@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Confer
 ences\,Exhibits\,Lectures/Seminars\,Meetings
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgASaZQ%2A7wCukl9Lu9hg8V81.jpg
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:Divis
 ion of Cardiology\nOffice of Continuing Medical Education\nOffice of Fac
 ulty Affairs\nUW School of Medicine
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Target Audience";ID=42285;TYPE=SingleLine:Pri
 mary Care\, Family Medicine\, Internists\, Allied Health Professionals\,
  residents\, fellows
DTSTAMP:20260402T112703Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: South Lake Un
 ion Campus - Orin Smith Auditorium\nAccessibility Contact: UW Interprofe
 ssional Continuing Education  ipce@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Conferences\,Exh
 ibits\,Lectures/Seminars\,Meetings\nEvent sponsors: Division of Cardiolo
 gy\nOffice of Continuing Medical Education\nOffice of Faculty Affairs\nU
 W School of Medicine\nTarget Audience: Primary Care\, Family Medicine\, 
 Internists\, Allied Health Professionals\, residents\, fellows\nLink: ht
 tps://uw.cloud-cme.com/MJ2609\n\nThis course is tailored for a cardiac e
 lectrophysiology\, cardiology\, internist\, emergency medicine and first
  responder audience and is intended to provide practical\, up-to-date in
 formation on sudden cardiac death risk assessment and management. World-
 class faculty from the University of Washington School of Medicine will 
 teach participants using lectures and an audience response system to enc
 ourage interactive dialogue. Recent evidence in risk assessment of sudde
 n cardiac death\, and treatment options for susceptible patients and sur
 vivors will be reviewed. Practical issues including selecting which pati
 ents need permanent implantable defibrillators\, wearable defibrillators
 \, the impact of modern guideline directed medical therapy for heart fai
 lure on sudden death risk will be covered.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
