BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Grow a Cut Flower Garden at Home (in-person)
LOCATION:Center for Urban Horticulture Complex (CUH)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260530T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260530T120000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_f280261c9
 cfd
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:UW Botanic Gard
 ens Event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus location";ID=30032;TYPE=CustomAsset:Ce
 nter for Urban Horticulture Complex (CUH)
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:urbhort@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Presenter";ID=30525;TYPE=SingleLine:Sarah Nay
 ani
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Contact Information";ID=30526;TYPE=SingleLine
 :urbhort@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Ticket Link";ID=30528;TYPE=Url:https://apps.i
 deal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_f280261c9cfd
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event image";ID=40;TYPE=Image:https://www.tru
 mba.com/i/DgCAc1KY-0GIcHp65WlanPOg.jpg
DTSTAMP:20260324T151151Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Center fo
 r Urban Horticulture Complex (CUH)\nAccessibility Contact: urbhort@uw.ed
 u\nPresenter: Sarah Nayani\nContact Information: urbhort@uw.edu\nTicket 
 Link: https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_f280261
 c9cfd\nLink: https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_
 f280261c9cfd\n\nCost: $45\nAdvance registration required\nFinancial aid 
 slots available on a first-come\, first-served basis\nREGISTER ONLINE: 
 \nhttps://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_f280261c9cfd
 \n\nEnjoy homegrown blooms from your backyard to spread throughout your 
 home and share with friends and family! In this class\, you will be guid
 ed through planning a cut garden space\, starting seeds at home\, harves
 ting flowers and foliage\, and the basics of arranging. Plus\, we’ll pra
 ctice planting some summer-loving flowers for you to take home!\n\nInstr
 uctor Sarah Nayani runs Grow Girl Seattle\, a seasonal flower growing an
 d arranging studio\, and chats with other flower growers and florists on
  her podcast\, Flower Friends. Each year she grows thousands of flower a
 nd foliage stems in her small home garden\, and designs textural and fra
 grant bouquets and arrangements for clients. She loves learning from the
  garden and continues to be amazed by the jaw-dropping beauty that the t
 iniest of seeds can bloom into.\n\nThis in-person class will be held at 
 the Center for Urban Horticulture.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
