DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nAccessibility Contact: urb
 hort@uw.edu\nPresenter: Constance Sidles\nContact Information: urbhort@u
 w.edu\nTicket Link: https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9K
 H-5PTF_8738c309064f\nLink: https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TG
 Y2T_K9KH-5PTF_8738c309064f\n\nCost: $25 - Advance registration required.
 \nFinancial aid slots available on a first-come\, first-served basis\nRE
 GISTER ONLINE: \nhttps://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5
 PTF_8738c309064f\nThe Bald Eagle is our most beloved bird\, the emblem o
 f our country. Almost as admired are their cousins\, the Golden Eagles. 
 But do these apex predators deserve their noble reputations? Benjamin Fr
 anklin believed eagles were the opposite of honorable\, nothing more tha
 n thieves\, and wanted the turkey as our national bird. So\, noble kings
 /queens of the sky or brazen thieves? You be the judge. Come hear master
  birder Connie Sidles tell you all about the eagles of Washington.\nNew 
 to Zoom or need more information? Get Started Here.: \nhttps://support.z
 oom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0061316\n\nAll times ar
 e Pacific Time.\n\nAccessibility: Closed captioning (through Zoom) is av
 ailable for all of our online classes. This class will be recorded and a
 vailable for registrants for 2 weeks after the class date.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
