BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FOOD SYSTEMS SEMINAR:  Reimagining Nutrition Assistance: Future 
 Directions for Food Security Policy
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260603T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260603T142000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://foodsystems.uw.edu/seminar/
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Generic UW Even
 t
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event interval";ID=30051;TYPE=CustomAsset:Sin
 gle day event
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Campus room";ID=28429;TYPE=SingleLine:Check M
 y Plan for location
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Accessibility Contact";ID=62969;TYPE=SingleLi
 ne:nutr@uw.edu
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=30073;TYPE=CustomAsset:Lectur
 es/Seminars
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event sponsors";ID=30383;TYPE=MultiLine:Schoo
 l of Public Health Food Systems\, Nutrition\, and Health program
DTSTAMP:20260320T104519Z
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: Check My Plan
  for location\nAccessibility Contact: nutr@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Lectures
 /Seminars\nEvent sponsors: School of Public Health Food Systems\, Nutrit
 ion\, and Health program\nLink: https://foodsystems.uw.edu/seminar/\n\nR
 eimagining Nutrition Assistance: Future Directions for Food Security Pol
 icy\n\nSpeaker:\nKatie Rains\, director\, Food Systems Initiatives\, Was
 hington State Department of Agriculture\n\nThis session is offered as pa
 rt of the weekly series on: "Food and Nutrition Security: Understanding
 \, Measuring and Reimagining Nutrition Assistance in the U.S."\n\nIf you 
 care about how food-related safety nets succeed—or fail—this seminar off
 ers tools to understand today’s landscape and imagine a better one.\n\nH
 ow is food and nutrition security defined\, measured\, and funded in the
  United States—and how do those choices shape real‑world hunger and heal
 th?\n\nThis seminar explores the nation’s major nutrition assistance pro
 grams—SNAP\, WIC\, school meals\, and the charitable food system. Learn 
 how these programs work\, who they reach\, and why their impacts vary ac
 ross states and communities.\n\nAll UW students\, faculty\, and staff ar
 e welcome to attend the seminar. Check MyPlan for location information.
CATEGORIES:UW Seattle Campus Events
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/199097617
X-TRUMBA-LINK:https://www.washington.edu/calendar/?trumbaEmbed=view%3dev
 ent%26eventid%3d199097617
