DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Center fo
 r Urban Horticulture Complex (CUH)\nAccessibility Contact: urbhort@uw.ed
 u\nPresenter: Melissa Galbraith\nContact Information: urbhort@uw.edu\nTi
 cket Link: https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF_af
 a643469ec1\nLink: https://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-
 5PTF_afa643469ec1\n\nClass Cost: $50\, pre-registration required \nREGIS
 TER ONLINE: \nhttps://apps.ideal-logic.com/uwbg?key=2WSB-TGY2T_K9KH-5PTF
 _afa643469ec1\nLimited financial aid slots offered on a first-come\, fir
 st-serve basis.\n\nCalling all cactus lovers! Learn beginner and advance
 d embroidery in this cactus-inspired workshop with fiber artist Melissa 
 Galbraith of MCreativeJ: https://www.mcreativej.com/. This two-hour\, ha
 nds-on workshop covers a variety of beginner-friendly embroidery stitche
 s including the back stitch\, reverse chain stitch\, couching\, needle w
 eaving\, and more! Each attendee will receive a full kit. Kits include: 
 a wooden embroidery hoop\, cactus transfer designs\, embroidery needle\,
  full skeins of embroidery thread\, a surprise pattern fabric\, backing 
 materials\, and printed instructions.\nMelissa Galbraith is the fiber ar
 tist behind MCreativeJ. She was born and raised in the desert of Washing
 ton state where her mother instilled a love of making things by hand at 
 an early age. Melissa shares her love of nature through whimsical and mo
 dern hand embroidery kits\, workshops\, and her books: 3D Botanical Embr
 oidery & Stumpwork: \nhttps://urldefense.com/v3/__https://shop.mcreative
 j.com/products/book-pre-order-3d-botanical-embroidery-stumpwork-17-threa
 d-projects-to-make-wear-and-display__\;!!K-Hz7m0Vt54!gWsFBp3k8Cm6GFLBf8A
 7eiGdQy5bigbLJnY2tr6HS2-Y0tbKrBgrgrVnmFJqTIkui-wK7YPGB9ShwhEHLQ$\, DIY E
 mbroidered Shoes: \nhttps://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/www.mcreativej.co
 m/diy-embroidered-shoes-book__\;!!K-Hz7m0Vt54!iWGkDb69Uu2XNGONYkuOUIdAEA
 EEvbmmjlskUYlMZeFxNwnCGIBrAeCfQo87IFSrz1zXacT1U3jXbBMKqg$\, and How to E
 mbroider Texture and Pattern: \nhttps://urldefense.com/v3/__https:/www.m
 creativej.com/my-book__\;!!K-Hz7m0Vt54!g2KCWPMxm6WScMEw5CA6zpCdgge8E6wW0
 x7_dYIstug0lMcBuN6lLSV8RQOPPXwDLE8JLW6VEPh88jeOuHA-$. Melissa enjoys see
 ing makers fall in love with the needle arts\, especially that magical a
 h-ha moment of learning something new.
