DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus room: Online\nAcces
 sibility Contact: Deb Nelson\, nelsod6@uw.edu\, 206-685-9323\nEvent Type
 s: Special Events\,Workshops\nEvent sponsors: UW Biostatistics\nLink: ht
 tps://si.biostat.washington.edu/institutes/siscer/CR2604\n\nOver the pas
 t 7 decades\, the randomized clinical trial (RCT) has become the gold st
 andard for evaluation of new drugs\, biologics\, devices\, procedures\, 
 and behavioral interventions.  In a half-day short course\, two critical
 ly important topics will be discussed that have broad implications in th
 e design and conduct of clinical trials: the Design of Non-Inferiority T
 rials and the Prevention of Missing Data.
